post_text:
Twas the Night Before the First Day of School...
Welcome back Wildkats!
ARRIVAL
Tomorrow, August 26th is our 1st Day of School. Our doors will open at 7:20 AM. The tardy bell is at 7:45 AM.
Parents will not be allowed to go past the elementary entrance. You are welcome to walk them all the way up to the doors, where they will be greeted by staff members who will ensure they make it to breakfast, the gym, or their classroom.
We will have our Electronic Sign Playing, Welcome Back Wildkat Lawn Letters and Wildkat Photo Backdrop set up on the sidewalk outside the entrance. Please feel free to capture those first day of school pictures there!

If you would like to send lunch money please send that with your child in an envelope with their name on it.

King City Elementary
Now Hiring:
The King City R-1 School District is seeking to hire a paraprofessional for the elementary building for the 2020-2021 school year. This position will work alongside a certified teacher and assist with a variety of tasks to ensure the success of students. The successful candidate needs to have a minimum of 60 hours of college course work. Applications may be picked up at the new central office or online at the www.kingcityschools.org website. This position is open until filled. If interested please contact Ryan Anderson at ryananderson@kingcityschools.org.

Student Material Dropoff Last Day is Tomorrow!
When:
May 19th from 1:00-7:00 pm for 3rd-6th Graders
(If you have children in multiple grades, you can pick what day works best for you).
Where: KCE South Entrance Circle Drive, we will have tables set up and labeled for items.
What Items need to be returned: Chromebooks and Chargers, Hot Spots (If borrowed from the school), textbooks, classroom reading books, library books. assignment packets from 1st-2nd grade). We will collect lunch money for students in the negative. We will also have a Summer Boot-camp Information and sign up set that day.

King City Elementary Secretary Opening.
The King City R-1 School District is accepting applications for an elementary school secretary. Applications may be picked up at the school or on the district website (www.kingcityschools.org). The position begins in August 2020 or when the CDC states it is acceptable for school to resume. Applicants must be able to pass a background screening process. The position is open until filled. Questions regarding the position can be directed to Ryan Anderson at ryananderson@kingcityschools.org. Completed applications should be turned in to the superintendent’s office.

King City R-I School District
April 9 at 5:39 PM ·

King City patrons, you were made aware of a decision regarding the school year the same way I was, through Governor Parsons daily briefing. I was given no advanced notice. While I do believe it was likely inevitable that school would not take place within the school building for the remainder of the year, it did not provide the school with the opportunity to put out a proper notice.

Once I receive all of the details from the Department of Education I will make a formal declaration.

Please know we will do everything we can to recognize our seniors sometime later in the summer once conditions allow for it.

Please share on your accounts.

post_text:
PLEASE SHARE!
RAINY DAY Wildkat Indoor PE Challenge
Let’s see what you come up with!! Please share pictures in the comments.

Here are ten energy releasing physical activities that are appropriate to play indoors!
Build an obstacle course—use blankets, pillows, toy bins, and furniture to make tunnels or tasks to run around or jump into
Hop, skip, or roll from one room to another
Practice somersaults or jumping jacks
Dance to silly songs
Bean bag toss
Indoor hopscotch—use masking or electrical tape on non-carpeted floor
Act out animal motions—slither like a snake, kick like a donkey, swing your trunk like an elephant, etc.
Step aerobics—use a folded blanket to step up onto and have your child copy what you do
Yoga, or stretching
Balloon ball—hit the balloon into the air and don’t let it touch the ground
Of course, with any indoor physical activity, be sure your play space is a safe one by being somewhat large and clear of toys and sharp edged furniture.
